                    <p>
                        The game of chess is a fairly simple game. Each chess piece has a set number of ways it can
                        maneuver across the board. The player with the white chess pieces always makes the first move.
                        If a pieces' next move is able to capture the oppossing king, the king is said to be in check.
                        The only legal move is one that will allow the king to not be in check.
